ee years in Europe as a Staff Sergeant in the 283rd Engineering Combat Battalion before returning to graduate as valedictorian of the class of 1946.","number":1},{"header":"He married during a hurricane","body":"While skiing in Austria on a Fulbright scholarship, Perry Morgan met two American women who, on returning to New York, introduced him to their roommate Elisabeth Harrison. They were married on August 13, 1955, at St. Mary's Roman Catholic Church in Greenwich, Connecticut — during a hurricane. The marriage lasted 63 years.","number":2},{"header":"He converted his family's Jacobean estate into Princeton's","body":"In the 1980s, Perry Morgan converted Constitution Hill — his family's longtime Jacobean estate in Princeton — into an innovative clustered-housing community, the first of its kind in Princeton. The design was inspired by northern European principles that prioritized open space and privacy while preserving the historic structures and grounds.","number":3},{"header":"He made a limited-edition etching at age 13","body":"In approximately 1937, Alexander Perry Morgan Jr. — about 13 years old — created a small etching titled 'Landscape,' signed 'Alexander P. Morgan' and numbered 4/15, indicating a print run of fifteen. It was bequeathed to the Princeton University Art Museum by Junius S.","number":4}],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST061","institution_blurb":"St. Paul's School, where he developed his love of chemistry and rowing before Princeton."},{"institution_id":"INST023"}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Alexander Perry Morgan Jr.","first_name":"Alexander","last_name":"Morgan","suffix":"Jr.","middle_name":"Perry","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"alexander-morgan-jr-1924"},"HD1243":{"id":"HD1243","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calc